{
  "provider": {
    "type": "gemini"
  },
  "commit": {
    "commitLanguage": "english",
    "commitFormat": "conventional",
    "useCustomInstructions": true,
    "customInstructions": "Generate a Git commit message in ENGLISH that STRICTLY conforms to my commitlint config\n(Conventional Commits + scope-enum + max subject length 72).\n\nOutput format (exactly):\n<type>[optional scope][optional !]: <subject>\n\n[optional body]\n\n[optional footer]\n\nHARD RULES (must follow):\n1) Header must match:\n   type(scope): subject\n   OR\n   type: subject\n   OR (only for breaking change, feat/fix only):\n   type(scope)!: subject\n   OR\n   type!: subject\n\n2) Subject rules:\n   - Present tense, imperative mood (e.g. \"add\", \"fix\", \"update\")\n   - CRITICAL: Start with lowercase after <scope>: or type:\n     • CORRECT: feat(auth): add new login\n     • CORRECT: fix: resolve crash\n     • WRONG: feat(auth): Add new login\n     • WRONG: fix: Resolve crash\n   - No trailing period\n   - Max 72 characters (count the whole subject after \": \")\n   - Concise and specific\n\n3) Type MUST be one of:\n   feat | fix | refactor | build | chore | docs | style | perf | test | ci | revert\n\n4) Scope (optional):\n   - If provided, it MUST be exactly one of these values:\n     repo, deps, version, release, deploy, config, auth, backend, convex, core,\n     design, features, types, tests, ci, docs, convex\n   - If none applies, OMIT the scope entirely (do NOT invent custom scopes).\n\n5) Breaking changes:\n   - Allowed ONLY for type feat or fix\n   - Indicate breaking change with \"!\" in the header (e.g. feat(auth)!: ...)\n   - If you mark breaking change, include a footer line:\n    BREAKING CHANGE: <short explanation>\n\n6) Body (optional):\n   - Use ONLY if the change is not trivially small.\n   - Prefer bullet points:\n     - Each bullet starts with \"- \"\n     - Keep bullets short (aim <= 100 chars per line)\n     - Limit to 5 bullets\n   - Describe what changed and why (not a full diff dump).\n\n7) Footer (optional):\n   - If referencing issues, add ONE footer line using this prefix:\n     closed: #<id>, #<id>\n     Example: closed: #31, #34\n   - If no issues, omit footer.\n\n8) Special case:\n   - chore(release): ... is acceptable (it is ignored by commitlint),\n     but ONLY use it for actual release commits.\n\nType selection guidance:\n- docs: documentation-only changes (README, *.md, docs/*)\n- feat: new user-facing capability/feature\n- fix: bug fix\n- refactor: restructuring without behavior change\n- build: build system / tooling / deps that affect builds\n- chore: maintenance that doesn't fit above (non-feature, non-fix)\n- style: formatting only (no behavior change)\n- perf: performance improvements\n- test: add/update tests\n- ci: CI pipeline/config changes\n- revert: revert a previous commit (describe what is reverted)\n\nExamples (scope must be from the allowed list, subject must start with lowercase):\n- docs: update setup instructions\n- feat(auth): add magic link login\n- fix(convex): handle null transaction category\n- feat(convex)!: change webhook signature validation\n  BREAKING CHANGE: webhook secret must be configured\n- chore(release): v1.8.0\n\nNow generate the best single commit message for the provided changes.\nReturn ONLY the commit message text, nothing else.",
    "onlyStagedChanges": true,
    "autoCommit": false,
    "autoPush": false,
    "promptForRefs": false
  },
  "gemini": {
    "model": "gemini-2.5-flash"
  },
  "codestral": {
    "model": "codestral-latest"
  },
  "openai": {
    "model": "gpt-3.5-turbo",
    "baseUrl": "https://api.openai.com/v1"
  },
  "ollama": {
    "baseUrl": "http://localhost:11434",
    "model": "llama3.2"
  },
  "telemetry": {
    "enabled": false
  }
}
